cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with the transmission of a bivariate Gaussian source over a multiple-access channel with conferencing encoders, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM) aspects. The use of unidirectional conferencing encoders also relates to networked systems (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the optimization of distortion pairs and the evaluation of asymptotics involve machine learning (cs.LG) techniques.
